#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:1
msgid "Using _Black_ with other tools"
msgstr "在其他工具中使用 _Black_"

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:3
msgid "Black compatible configurations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:5
msgid ""
"All of Black's changes are harmless (or at least, they should be), but a few "
"do conflict against other tools. It is not uncommon to be using other tools "
"alongside _Black_ like linters and type checkers. Some of them need a bit of "
"tweaking to resolve the conflicts. Listed below are _Black_ compatible "
"configurations in various formats for the common tools out there."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:11
msgid ""
"**Please note** that _Black_ only supports the TOML file format for its "
"configuration (e.g. `pyproject.toml`). The provided examples are to only "
"configure their corresponding tools, using **their** supported file formats."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:15
msgid ""
"Compatible configuration files can be [found here](https://github.com/psf/"
"black/blob/main/docs/compatible_configs/)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:18
msgid "isort"
msgstr "isort"

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:20
msgid ""
"[isort](https://pypi.org/p/isort/) helps to sort and format imports in your "
"Python code. _Black_ also formats imports, but in a different way from "
"isort's defaults which leads to conflicting changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:24
msgid "Profile"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:26
msgid ""
"Since version 5.0.0, isort supports [profiles](https://pycqa.github.io/isort/"
"docs/configuration/profiles.html) to allow easy interoperability with common "
"code styles. You can set the black profile in any of the [config files]"
"(https://pycqa.github.io/isort/docs/configuration/config_files.html) "
"supported by isort. Below, an example for `pyproject.toml`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:32
msgid ""
"[tool.isort]\n"
"profile = \"black\"\n"
msgstr ""
"[tool.isort]\n"
"profile = \"black\"\n"

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:37
msgid "Custom Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:39
msgid ""
"If you're using an isort version that is older than 5.0.0 or you have some "
"custom configuration for _Black_, you can tweak your isort configuration to "
"make it compatible with _Black_. Below, an example for `.isort.cfg`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:43
msgid ""
"multi_line_output = 3\n"
"include_trailing_comma = True\n"
"force_grid_wrap = 0\n"
"use_parentheses = True\n"
"ensure_newline_before_comments = True\n"
"line_length = 88\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:52
#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:153
#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:235
#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:264
msgid "Why those options above?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:54
msgid ""
"_Black_ wraps imports that surpass `line-length` by moving identifiers onto "
"separate lines and by adding a trailing comma after each. A more detailed "
"explanation of this behaviour can be [found here](../the_black_code_style/"
"current_style.md#how-black-wraps-lines)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:59
msgid ""
"isort's default mode of wrapping imports that extend past the `line_length` "
"limit is \"Grid\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:62
msgid ""
"from third_party import (lib1, lib2, lib3,\n"
"                         lib4, lib5, ...)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:67
msgid ""
"This style is incompatible with _Black_, but isort can be configured to use "
"a different wrapping mode called \"Vertical Hanging Indent\" which looks "
"like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:70
msgid ""
"from third_party import (\n"
"    lib1,\n"
"    lib2,\n"
"    lib3,\n"
"    lib4,\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:79
msgid ""
"This style is _Black_ compatible and can be achieved by `multi-line-output = "
"3`. Also, as mentioned above, when wrapping long imports _Black_ puts a "
"trailing comma and uses parentheses. isort should follow the same behaviour "
"and passing the options `include_trailing_comma = True` and `use_parentheses "
"= True` configures that."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:84
msgid ""
"The option `force_grid_wrap = 0` is just to tell isort to only wrap imports "
"that surpass the `line_length` limit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:87
msgid ""
"Finally, isort should be told to wrap imports when they surpass _Black_'s "
"default limit of 88 characters via `line_length = 88` as well as "
"`ensure_newline_before_comments = True` to ensure spacing import sections "
"with comments works the same as with _Black_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:92
msgid ""
"**Please note** `ensure_newline_before_comments = True` only works since "
"isort >= 5 but does not break older versions so you can keep it if you are "
"running previous versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:95
#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:189
#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:239
