#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:137
msgid "pycodestyle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:139
msgid ""
"[pycodestyle](https://pycodestyle.pycqa.org/) is a code linter. It warns you "
"of syntax errors, possible bugs, stylistic errors, etc. For the most part, "
"pycodestyle follows [PEP 8](https://peps.python.org/pep-0008/) when warning "
"about stylistic errors. There are a few deviations that cause "
"incompatibilities with _Black_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:144
#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:258
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:146
msgid ""
"max-line-length = 88\n"
"ignore = E203,E701\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:155
msgid "`max-line-length`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:157
msgid ""
"As with isort, pycodestyle should be configured to allow lines up to the "
"length limit of `88`, _Black_'s default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:160
msgid "`E203`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:162
msgid ""
"In some cases, as determined by PEP 8, _Black_ will enforce an equal amount "
"of whitespace around slice operators. Due to this, pycodestyle will raise "
"`E203 whitespace before ':'` warnings. Since this warning is not PEP 8 "
"compliant, it should be disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:167
msgid "`E701` / `E704`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:169
msgid ""
"_Black_ will collapse implementations of classes and functions consisting "
"solely of `..` to a single line. This matches how such examples are "
"formatted in PEP 8. It remains true that in all other cases Black will "
"prevent multiple statements on the same line, in accordance with PEP 8 "
"generally discouraging this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:174
msgid ""
"However, `pycodestyle` does not mirror this logic and may raise `E701 "
"multiple statements on one line (colon)` in this situation. Its disabled-by-"
"default `E704 multiple statements on one line (def)` rule may also raise "
"warnings and should not be enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:179
msgid "`W503`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:181
msgid ""
"When breaking a line, _Black_ will break it before a binary operator. This "
"is compliant with PEP 8 as of [April 2016](https://github.com/python/peps/"
"commit/"
"c59c4376ad233a62ca4b3a6060c81368bd21e85b#diff-64ec08cc46db7540f18f2af46037f599). "
"There's a disabled-by-default warning in Flake8 which goes against this PEP "
"8 recommendation called `W503 line break before binary operator`. It should "
"not be enabled in your configuration. You can use its counterpart `W504 line "
"break after binary operator` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:191
msgid ""
"<details>\n"
"<summary>setup.cfg, .pycodestyle, tox.ini</summary>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:194
msgid ""
"[pycodestyle]\n"
"max-line-length = 88\n"
"ignore = E203,E701\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:202
msgid "Flake8"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:204
msgid ""
"[Flake8](https://pypi.org/p/flake8/) is a wrapper around multiple linters, "
"including pycodestyle. As such, it has many of the same issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:207
msgid "Bugbear"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:209
msgid ""
"It's recommended to use [the Bugbear plugin](https://github.com/PyCQA/flake8-"
"bugbear) and enable [its B950 check](https://github.com/PyCQA/flake8-"
"bugbear#opinionated-warnings#:~:text=you%20expect%20it.-,B950,-"
"%3A%20Line%20too%20long) instead of using Flake8's E501, because it aligns "
"with [Black's 10% rule](labels/line-length)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:215
msgid "Install Bugbear and use the following config:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:217
msgid ""
"[flake8]\n"
"max-line-length = 80\n"
"extend-select = B950\n"
"extend-ignore = E203,E501,E701\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:224
msgid "Minimal Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:226
msgid ""
"In cases where you can't or don't want to install Bugbear, you can use this "
"minimally compatible config:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:229
#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:244
msgid ""
"[flake8]\n"
"max-line-length = 88\n"
"extend-ignore = E203,E701\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:237
msgid "See [the pycodestyle section](labels/why-pycodestyle-warnings) above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:241
msgid ""
"<details>\n"
"<summary>.flake8, setup.cfg, tox.ini</summary>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:252
msgid "Pylint"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:254
msgid ""
"[Pylint](https://pypi.org/p/pylint/) is also a code linter like Flake8. It "
"has many of the same checks as Flake8 and more. It particularly has more "
"formatting checks regarding style conventions like variable naming."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:260
msgid "max-line-length = 88\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:266
msgid ""
"Pylint should be configured to only complain about lines that surpass `88` "
"characters via `max-line-length = 88`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:269
msgid ""
"If using `pylint<2.6.0`, also disable `C0326` and `C0330` as these are "
"incompatible with _Black_ formatting and have since been removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:274
msgid ""
"<details>\n"
"<summary>pylintrc</summary>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:277
msgid ""
"[format]\n"
"max-line-length = 88\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:287
msgid ""
"[pylint]\n"
"max-line-length = 88\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_other_tools.md:297
msgid ""
"[tool.pylint.format]\n"
"max-line-length = \"88\"\n"
msgstr ""
